      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That burning sensation during a HIIT set is primarily caused by the rapid accumulation of inorganic protons (H+) as the muscles switch to anaerobic metabolism, lowering the local pH and activating acid-sensing nerve endings. You might feel like you are getting \"clogged\" because this acidic environment inhibits key enzymes like glycolytic enzymes and causes calcium release in muscle fibers, which transiently increases fatigue and limits power output. It is largely a neurological and chemical irritant from the local environment rather than serum lactate itself physically blocking your movement.",
